<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="last-adj">last <strong><em>adj</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /lɑːst/    美 /læst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>最后的；仅剩的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I caught the last bus home. 
我赶上了回家的末班车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Can I have the last piece of cake? 
我把最后一块蛋糕吃了好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please read <strong>the last but one</strong> paragraph. 
请读倒数第二段。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>最近的；上一个的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>last night / week</strong> / summer 
昨晚/上个星期/去年夏天</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Technology has affected our life greatly in / over the last 20 years.
近20年来科技极大地改变了我们的生活。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>最不可能的；最不适合的</strong></h4>
<p>used to emphasize that sb / sth is the least likely or suitable：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was <strong>the last person</strong> in the world he wanted to accept assistance from.
在这个世界上他最不想接受帮助的人是我。</p><footer>2016 全国改</footer></div></div>